      <div class="quotetitle">Devin wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">traser wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">QUOTE: Disclosure: I, Cyrus Farivar, and Ars contributor Tim Lee both own some bitcoins.<br /><br />Why the disclosure? Do journalists for financial papers, when writing about fluctuations in American currency write &quot;Disclosure: My salary and retirement fund are both in US dollars.&quot; Seems a bit odd..</div><br />1. How often do Ars writers tackle stories about currency that is not bitcoin?<br />2. It should probably be assumed that a person that exists in the state that mandates a particular currency would possess amounts of that currency. Bitcoin is not (as far as I know) an official currency in the US, or elsewhere, and there could be a real concern for people with an interest in the currency to encourage speculation in it to drive up their own value.</div><br /><br />Sadly, I haven't yet needed to mention the fact that I hold Z$50,000,000,000 (<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://bit.ly/VARTIQ">http://bit.ly/VARTIQ</a><!-- m -->). :-)
      
    </div>
