<li class="thin-divide-bottom comment neutral read"
  data-post-score="1"
  data-post-negative="0"
  data-post-positive="1"
  data-post-id="23935919" data-poster-id="327995" id="comment-23935919">
  <header class="byline">
    
    <span class="author" data-post-author="danielravennest"><a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=327995&amp;sid=96851eef763b57a86e87b045f5779382">danielravennest</a></span><span class="rank">Ars Centurion</span>
      <aside class="icons">
        
        <a href="http://arstechnica.com/business/2013/02/internet-archive-says-employees-have-asked-to-be-paid-partially-in-bitcoin/?comments=1&post=23935919#comment-23935919" title="2013-02-22T14:01:29-06:00" class="timeago datetime">Fri Feb 22, 2013 2:01 pm</a>
        
        <span class="hidden-icon-start"></span>
        
      </aside>
    </header>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="quotetitle">yoshua wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What's the benefit of being paid in bitcoins? Tax evasion? Of course there is certainly a real risk: another currency collapse.</div><br /><br />The Internet Archive would not want to risk their non-profit status, so they will likely report it properly to the IRS.  How to deal with &quot;payment in kind&quot; (anything other than dollars) is well understood by them.<br /><br />Aside from the geek value of having a screen popup that says &quot;You've got money&quot;, if you work in a different country than the employer, or you want to send funds to relatives, it's easier because bitcoin is transnational, and you don't have to mess with bank wires (expensive), western union, or PayPal (doesn't go everywhere) to cross borders.<br /><br />International transactions, and micro-transactions are the two places bitcoin is better than the alternatives.  For example, some topics on reddit.com have enabled bitcoin tips in the comments. Imagine that, getting money from other people for good comments!<br /><br />Also, you can order pizza with it: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://pizzaforcoins.com/">http://pizzaforcoins.com/</a><!-- m -->
      
    </div>
    <footer>
      <aside class="vote">
        
        <a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/ucp.php?mode=login&amp;return_to=http%3A%2F%2Farstechnica.com%2Fbusiness%2F2013%2F02%2Finternet-archive-says-employees-have-asked-to-be-paid-partially-in-bitcoin%2F%3Fcomments%3D1%26amp%3Bstart%3D0%23comment-23935919" class="vote_login vote_up_login" title="Login to vote up">up</a>
